## User Roles

| Role | Slug | Capabilities |
|------|------|-------------|
| Administrator | administrator | Full access |
| Coach / Customer | bsp_coach | Portal access, submit orders, manage own rosters |
| Designer | bsp_designer | Artwork queue access, proof uploads |
| Subscriber | subscriber | Registration only, pending approval |

## Naming Conventions

- Custom post types: `bsp_roster`, `bsp_team`, `bsp_artwork`, `bsp_order`
- Taxonomies: `bsp_sport`, `bsp_age_group`
- REST namespace: `battle-sports/v1`
- Option keys: `bsp_*`
- Transient keys: `bsp_*`
- Meta keys: `_bsp_*`
- Hook names: `bsp_*`

## AI Development Guidelines (Cursor + Claude)

- Always read ARCHITECTURE.md before making structural changes
- Update ARCHITECTURE.md when adding new files, CPTs, endpoints, or roles
- Reference `gravityforms-export-2026-03-01.json` when rebuilding intake logic — all field
  labels, choices, and conditional logic are documented there
- When building intake forms natively, mirror the existing GF field structure exactly before
  enhancing — backwards compat with existing submissions matters
- Prefer small, focused commits — one feature or fix per session
- Write PHPDoc on all public methods
- Write inline comments for non-obvious logic
- Do not remove existing Gravity Forms hooks without confirming migration is complete

## Make.com / Monday.com Integration

- Webhook endpoint: `POST /wp-json/battle-sports/v1/webhook/make`
- Monday.com board IDs and column IDs stored in wp_options under `bsp_monday_config`
- Artwork status flow: `submitted → in_queue → in_progress → proof_sent → approved → complete`

## Security Requirements

- All REST endpoints require authentication unless explicitly public
- File uploads validated by MIME type and extension whitelist: jpg, jpeg, png, pdf, ai, eps
- Max upload size enforced at application layer (50MB)
- All admin pages check `current_user_can('manage_options')`
- Portal pages check `is_user_logged_in()` and role capability

